The model and production run information may also be coded if the code and/or the uncoded information is available
to any Consumer Product Safety Commission representative immediately upon request at the specified address.

If it is physically or technologically impracticable to permanently mark a children's product or fireworks product,
the required information shall be permanently marked or printed on (1) the immediate container of the product, (2)
any container sold with and intended to be used with the product, and (3) any container sold with and intended to be used
for storage of the product after purchase.

